@hunterschafer has been keeping busy, between wrapping up her character Jules's storyline on ‘Euphoria’ as well as her roles in movies like ‘Mother Mary.’ She's also been the face of @muglerofficial's legendary Angel scent franchise. Next up: She's the spokesperson for Angel Blush Eau de Parfum and is set to star in the new #BladeRunner TV series and #TomFord's next movie, to name a few projects on her roster.

The actress has also heard what everybody online has had to say about the ‘Euphoria’ finale—particularly her character Jules's painting of @zendaya's Rue. “I understand how that could potentially be perceived that way,” she tells ELLE. 

Before she takes over our screens again, Schafer chatted with us to clear up that Rue fan theory, share the smell she associates with first love, and explain how she accesses divine femininity. Read the full interview at the link in bio.

