@marabrockakil—the mastermind behind ‘Girlfriends,’ ‘The Game,’ and, most recently, @netflix’s ‘Forever’—has spent her career creating a canon of compelling, complex, deeply human Black female characters. Now, at 56, Akil is putting pen to paper with her debut novel, The Revelation of Dionne Daphne, out June 30.
Through her most vulnerable work yet, Akil explores themes of sexual abuse, family trauma, liberation, and the dark side of the American dream, drawing from puzzle pieces she has been quietly collecting for years.
In a wide-ranging conversation, Akil opens up to ELLE about this new chapter, the parts of herself she poured into Dionne, and the revelations she hopes readers find between the pages. Read the full interview at the link in bio.

