@undercover_lab is revisiting one of its greatest artist collaborations. Eleven years after Jun Takahashi first worked with Belgian painter Michaël Borremans, the duo returns for Spring/Summer 2027 with a fresh collection that proves great art on clothing doesn't have to feel forced.⁠
⁠
Borremans' haunting paintings appear across UNDERCOVER staples, from parkas and knits to jeans and oversized shorts, using new artworks that have never appeared on clothing before. More than another fashion-art crossover, it's a reminder that Takahashi, an accomplished artist himself, still knows how to make this kind of collaboration feel genuinely special.

