Prada’s Spring/Summer 2024 collection proved that true luxury doesn’t need to shout.
Designed by Miuccia Prada and Raf Simons, the collection explored softness, fluidity, and freedom through weightless fabrics, modern tailoring, and silhouettes that celebrated the natural movement of the body. Blending craftsmanship with quiet innovation, it offered a refined vision of contemporary elegance that continues to influence fashion today.
@prada #Prada #Luxurious

@celine closed Paris Men’s—and yes, it was hot. Literally and otherwise. For SS27, artistic director Michael Rider delivered his first standalone menswear runway for the house, stepping out of the co-ed format and into something more defined.
And as always, the styling was exciting, the tailoring sexy, and the details to-die-for. Drop your thoughts.
